+        for attempt in range(400):
+            # Band-stratified bearing. Sampling bearing uniformly and rejecting
+            # on the scene rectangle biases HARD toward centre: wide bearings
+            # only fit at short range, so they get rejected more often. Measured
+            # on v4 (uniform +-42.5 deg): 45% of goals landed within 10 deg and
+            # only 15% beyond 30 deg. A centre-clustered goal lets the policy
+            # succeed by driving roughly straight and never forces the turn that
+            # takes the goal out of the FOV -- exactly the case goal memory
+            # exists for.
+            #
+            # So draw the BAND first, then a distance that fits it.
+            # Narrow scenes cannot host a peripheral goal at all: `corridor` is
+            # 1.2 m wide, so 30 deg at 2 m already exits the hallway. After half
